Comment (src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue:305):
**[medium] Diagrams added to a 404-reset grouping never render — `addDiagram`'s `push` mutates a plain object inside a `shallowRef`.**

`useDataApi`'s `data` is a **`shallowRef`**. Objects that arrive via a 200 response are reactive proxies (they come out of `useAxios`'s deep ref), but this `{ diagrams: [] }` assigned on 404 — and the `initialData: {}` — are **plain objects**. `addDiagram()` (line ~392, unchanged code) then does `grouping.value.diagrams.push(created)`: against a plain object that mutation triggers nothing, so after the API returns 201 the success toast fires but **no diagram card appears until a full page refresh**. Reproduced on the dev stack with the ToDo Demo SSP. `deleteDiagram()`'s `grouping.value.diagrams = ...filter(...)` has the same problem (property write on a plain object).

Fix: replace the mutations with an immutable reassignment of the whole ref value in both `addDiagram` and `deleteDiagram`:

```ts
grouping.value = {
  ...(grouping.value ?? {}),
  diagrams: [...(grouping.value?.diagrams ?? []), created],
} as Diagrammable;
```

Add a regression test that mocks the grouping fetch rejecting with 404 (so this reset runs), mocks the create POST returning a diagram, clicks Add Diagram, and asserts a diagram card renders — it must fail against the current `push` code.

Context: 'Add Diagram' on Network Architecture / Data Flow currently also fails server-side (the API 404s when the grouping row doesn't exist — no UI bug; fixed in compliance-framework/api#415 which auto-creates the grouping on first diagram POST). Once that lands, this reactivity bug is the only thing between the user and a working Add Diagram, since the 404-reset path is exactly the state those SSPs are in.
