Comment (src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue:28):
**[feature request] Per-diagram title (from OSCAL `caption`) + per-diagram hide/show — turn this header row into a real diagram card header.**

Each diagram currently renders as an anonymous box: this row holds only the Delete button, then the editor. Requested for this PR (applies to all three category groups):

1. **Title from `caption`**: show `diagram.caption` in this header row, falling back to a muted/italic "Untitled diagram" when empty; if `diagram.description` is non-empty show it as a smaller muted line (or tooltip). The OSCAL `Diagram` model already has `caption`/`description`, and `addDiagram` already POSTs `caption: ''`.
2. **Inline caption edit**: an Edit-title action (e.g. `pi-pencil` `TertiaryButton`) swapping the title for a volt `InputText` with save/cancel. Save PUTs via the existing per-category save executors (`saveABDiagram`/`saveNADiagram`/`saveDFDiagram`) sending **the full existing diagram with only `caption` changed** — `props` is where the drawio XML/PNG live (`ns: 'ccf'`, `ccf-diagram-xml`/`ccf-diagram-png`), so it must round-trip untouched (worth an explicit test asserting the PUT body retains the original props). Update the local grouping ref with the same immutable-reassignment style as the reactivity fix so the new title renders immediately. Empty caption is allowed (falls back to the placeholder).
3. **Hide/show per diagram**, like the category groups: clicking the header toggles the editor body. **Use `v-show`, NOT `v-if`/`CollapsableGroup`** — `DrawIODiagramEditor` keeps unsaved drawio state in its iframe and clears its XML cache in `onBeforeUnmount`, so a `v-if` collapse destroys unsaved work. A local `ref<Record<string, boolean>>` keyed by diagram uuid (mirroring `componentPanelsCollapsed` in ComponentsView) is fine; default expanded; add a chevron indicator; keep `@click.stop` on the action buttons; don't persist collapse state.

Keep all endpoints, the `useDeleteConfirmationDialog` wiring (its `itemName: diagram.caption || diagram.uuid` gets more useful with real captions), the category `CollapsableGroup` structure, and the save flow unchanged.

Suggested tests: caption rendering + fallback; caption edit PUTs with props preserved and updates the rendered title; collapse hides the editor via `v-show` (element still in the DOM with `display: none`, not removed).
Implementation guidance: In src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue, fix the shallowRef update bug in addDiagram and deleteDiagram by replacing nested mutations with whole-ref immutable assignment. In addDiagram, after createDiagram returns the created Diagram, resolve the target grouping as today, then assign grouping.value = { ...(grouping.value ?? {}), diagrams: [...(grouping.value?.diagrams ?? []), created] } as Diagrammable instead of pushing into grouping.value.diagrams. Ensure this also works when grouping.value is {} from initialData or { diagrams: [] } from the 404 reset. In deleteDiagram, after the delete call succeeds, assign grouping.value = { ...(grouping.value ?? {}), diagrams: (grouping.value?.diagrams ?? []).filter((item) => item.uuid !== diagram.uuid) } as Diagrammable instead of writing grouping.value.diagrams directly. Keep the prior design decision intact: do not seed a client-only placeholder diagram, keep authorizationBoundary initialData empty, keep 404 resets empty, and keep new diagrams created only through addDiagram and the POST endpoint. Add a focused regression test in src/views/system/__tests__/systemViews.spec.ts or the existing DiagramsView test file that mocks an optional diagram grouping fetch rejecting with 404, mocks the create diagram POST returning a diagram, clicks Add Diagram, and asserts that the new diagram card/editor renders immediately without a full reload.
